 Appearances (Goals). Mihai Roman (born 16 October 1984 in Braov) is a Romanian footballer who currently plays for Rapid Bucureti. Roman started his football career at the age of 17. He made his way up working hard, with the help of Razvan Lucescu, his former coach from FC Braov. Before signing to Braov, Roman was linked with other Liga I clubs such as FC Vaslui and Oelul Galai. After two great seasons, he received his first call-up for Romania in June 2009. Many teams have shown their interests in signing Mihai. Some of the teams were FC Timioara and CFR Cluj. On 27 June 2010, Roman signed for Rapid Bucureti together with his teammate Sabrin Sburlea. Roman made his debut for the Romania national football team in a 2010 FIFA World Cup qualification game on 6 June 2009 against Lithuania.
